	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				For everyone complaining about the increased weight of the Combine kits, what you don't realize is that combine kits are NOT things you carry stuff around in.  The low weight simply made them attractive as such.<BR>
<BR>
Really though, how many of you would carry stuff around in a spit?  A sewing kit?  You wouldn't.  The ash and gunk from the spit would make anything in there a blackened mess.  Highly unattractive.  And what's with the food in the sewing kit?  Come on, people, now we've got to clean the rations off the needle, dry out the thread since the water spilled on it.<BR>
<BR>
Picturing this as a real world and not as just numbers makes it more right.<BR>
<BR>
Frankly, I think it's a small price to pay to get safe combine buttons, when even at your most cautious, you could lose that valuable roll and cause more grief than a gain of 3.6wt.<BR>
<BR>
P.S., To the monks out there, don't even worry about bags early on if it bothers you that much.  Loot things that stack, or get smaller containers.  Tailored large bags are only .8 wt.  6 slots, AND give weight reduction!  So it's not 8 or 10 slots, it's still nice.<BR>
<BR>
--Kassara Stilfyre, 27th monk of the Ashen Order, member of Fantasy, Vazaelle.
				</font>
			</td>

