	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The changes to the trade containers is, IMO, excellent!  Notice that only the power-gamers are complaining about the change?<BR>
<BR>
Verant Interactive did have an alternative to the changes that they made which, IMO, would have been 'more realistic' but no less troublesome to the power-gamers (since the end effect would have been the same).  That alternative is implement a means so that only materials that can be used in a trade kit are able to be placed in a trade kit.  e.g. only pelts, patterns, silk, swatches, thread or silk rope in sewing kits.<BR>
<BR>
This would be slightly less of a burden on tradespeople, but still would restrict putting loot et. al. in the kits.  Verant Interactive simply took the simpler route.<BR>
<BR>
Note: I do have low strength characters that this affects, but I've been using bags and the like for the most part anyway so I'll only take a small weight hit when I log in.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
