			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				**Trade Containers**<BR>
Change it BACK! please! This mod has destroyed the value of carrying lightweight kits as containers, and for what? Some weenies whining because they can't control their mice? We've lived with the risk of destroying items for a ling time, and those that choose to take the risk, should be allowed that choice. I DO NOT need to be protected from my own stupidity. If I %#$% up a combine in a trade, I piss, I moan, but I have never complained to a GM. It's my own damn fault, and I do NOT need to be &quot;helped&quot; in that way. I do not need my hand held,  I do not need to be hand fed, I do not need my ass wiped for me, and I do NOT need someone taking my choice to take a risk away. If I want safety, I'll buy heavy bags and containters.<BR>
<BR>
 Please, please, please, give us back the freedom to choose. Give us a chance to frustrate ourselves on bad combines. Make it more difficult to find new trade recipes. Please give us our lightweight containers back. Remember the poor casters that are too damn weak to carry a worn great staff and a couple backpacks. Not to mention a little loot along with it. Please get rid of this mod, it is only good for placating sniveling, whining little idiots that can't accept responsibility for their own actions. I want my right to choose to take a risk.<BR>
<BR>
A very Enraged (and very weak) caster.<BR>
If ye agree with this please send this letter or something similar to eqfeedback@verant.com
